description: Test the power supply voltage rail inside the control module to confirm that a stable 12V supply is present. This will help rule out power instability as a cause of the oscillation., outcome='The measured voltage at Control Input Cable (+) is approximately 11.86 V, and at Control Input Cable (−) is approximately 0.012 V, indicating the supply rail is close to the expected 12V. The circuit simulation did not converge, showing instability or oscillation in the module. There are no detected polarity inversions based on the cable labels provided.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> ambient light sensor and surrounding environment,
description: Visually inspect the ambient light sensor and its immediate environment to check for intermittent or variable light exposure that may cause the relay to switch erratically. Look for possible sources of light fluctuations (e.g., moving shadows, reflections, variable illumination) near the sensor., outcome='The Ambient Light Sensor was visually inspected and no observable internal fault was found. The circuit is currently unstable or oscillating, but based on this inspection, intermittent or variable light exposure sources around the sensor were not specifically identified.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> control module relay,
description: Visually inspect the relay and its immediate circuitry for signs of physical damage, miswiring, or incorrect installation. Look for any mechanical or electrical irregularities, such as burned contacts, loose connections, or oscillations in the relay armature., outcome='Visual inspection reveals no observable internal faults or physical damage to the control relay, sensor bias resistor, or any of the inspected cables. The Control Input Cable (+) and Control Input Cable (−) both have their positive ports connected, while the Control Output Cable (+) and Control Output Cable (−) have their negative ports connected—no polarity inversion detected based on available connection details. Note: The circuit is reported as unstable or oscillating, but no visible miswiring or mechanical faults were found.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> op-amp/comparator in the control module,
description: Test the operation of the op-amp or comparator driving the relay in the control module by measuring the voltages at its output and both inputs while the circuit is operating. Look for abnormal oscillation or instability indicative of a malfunction or incorrect feedback., outcome='The circuit is unstable or oscillating, as indicated by the simulation not converging. The voltage measurements at the relay, light sensor, and sensor bias resistor have been successfully recorded. No polarity inversion is detected based on the given measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module (feedback and grounding),
description: Test all ground connections and feedback paths in the control module circuit for continuity, correct voltage, and shorts to other signals. An unstable or oscillating op-amp/comparator can be caused by poor grounding or unintended feedback loops., outcome='All tested ground and negative-side connections show nominal continuity (0.1 Ω) and no unexpected resistance, and point-to-point testing between them confirms a short as expected. The sensor bias resistor measures correct resistance (10 kΩ) and meaningful voltage, and the control relay shows correct continuity and voltage. No polarity inversion is detected in any tested cable or port.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=395.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('short_ports', 20.0), ('short_ports', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
